---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="QSol Analytics privacy policy. How we collect, use, and protect your personal data."
>
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="container-narrow prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-light"><strong>Last updated:</strong> February 2024</p>

      <p>
        QSol Analytics ("we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your personal data when you use our website or services.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Controller</h2>
      <p>
        The data controller responsible for your personal data is:<br />
        David J. McCann<br />
        QSol Analytics<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:david@qsol-analytics.com">david@qsol-analytics.com</a>
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <h3>Information you provide</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Contact form submissions: name, email, company name, message</li>
        <li>Booking requests: name, email, scheduling preferences</li>
        <li>Email correspondence: content of emails you send us</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
      <p>
        We use Plausible Analytics, a privacy-friendly analytics service that does not use cookies and does not collect personal data. We collect:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Page views and referral sources (aggregated, anonymous)</li>
        <li>Country of origin (from IP address, not stored)</li>
        <li>Device type and browser (aggregated)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To respond to your enquiries and provide requested services</li>
        <li>To send you information about our services (only with your consent)</li>
        <li>To improve our website and services</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contract:</strong> Processing necessary to respond to your enquiry or provide services</li>
        <li><strong>Consent:</strong> Where you have opted in to marketing communications</li>
        <li><strong>Legitimate interest:</strong> Website analytics and service improvement</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal data. We may share data with:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Service providers who assist in operating our website (hosting, form processing)</li>
        <li>Professional advisors where required</li>
        <li>Authorities if required by law</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Contact form submissions: 2 years from last contact</li>
        <li>Analytics data: 26 months (aggregated, no personal data)</li>
        <li>Client project data: as agreed in project terms</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Under GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access your personal data</li>
        <li>Rectify inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Request erasure of your data</li>
        <li>Restrict or object to processing</li>
        <li>Data portability</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent at any time</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:david@qsol-analytics.com">david@qsol-analytics.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        We use Plausible Analytics, which does not use cookies. For more information, see our <a href="/cookies/">Cookie Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Complaints</h2>
      <p>
        If you have concerns about how we handle your data, please contact us first. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. The latest version will always be available on this page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
